13 longum et unum: The reigns of these three emperors exceeded one year but lasted less than two (June 6. 68 —Dec. 20. 69), hence styled ‘that one memorably long year'3 memorable, because so many stirring events occurred within 80 short a period. Observe that ‘unus' in Tac. does not precede, except when joined to a numeral, so always in the phrase ‘unus . . . alter,' or to ‘idem’ (e. g. c. 22 26 G. 24). Cf. 0. 34 31 with note and 41 16.
